cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel coding strategy to mitigate the impact of straggling decoders in the cloud computing platform. The upper bounds on the Frame Error Rate (FER) are derived by assuming a binary symmetric channel for uplink communications. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies the uplink of a cloud radio access network (C-RAN) architecture and proposes a coding strategy to improve the performance of the network. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the problem of straggling decoders in a cloud computing platform, which is a common issue in distributed computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a coding strategy to improve the performance of a cloud computing system, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper deals with the problem of straggling decoders in a cloud computing platform, which can be seen as a computational complexity problem.
